trans-unit.source: Provides <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> objects for the different states of the check box control.
This class cannot be inherited.

Each property of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Button.CheckBox> class returns a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> for a different state of the check box control.
Gets a visual style element that represents a disabled check box in the checked state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Button.CheckBox.CheckedDisabled%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a disabled check box in the checked state.
Gets a visual style element that represents a hot check box in the checked state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Button.CheckBox.CheckedHot%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a hot check box in the checked state.
Gets a visual style element that represents a normal check box in the checked state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Button.CheckBox.CheckedNormal%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a normal check box in the checked state.
Gets a visual style element that represents a pressed check box in the checked state.

You can use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement> returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.Button.CheckBox.CheckedPressed%2A> property to create a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleRenderer>.
A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a pressed check box in the checked state.
Gets a visual style element that represents a disabled check box in the indeterminate state.

A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a disabled check box in the indeterminate state.

A <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement"></xref> that represents a hot check box in the indeterminate state.
